ers to implement them without knowing what intelligence might have to say about their likely efficacy and unintended consequences would be exceedingly difficult intelligence derived information and insights should not dictate the goals of grand strategy but they should inform decisions about what to do how to do it and what to look for in order to assess how well or badly the strategy is working downloads pdf+ intelligence and grand strategy by thomas fingar modified january 2012 pdf fingar__intelligence_and_grand pdf 128.2 kb html+ go to site external http www sciencedirect com scienc parent research terrorism insurgency and homeland security search cisac publications everything publications of interest soviet military strategy yi zhou cisac 1989 uses and nonuses of intelligence the amos kovacs cisac 1996 reforming intelligence obstacles to democratic control and effectiveness thomas c bruneau steven c boraz university of texas press austin 2007 buy+ cover eyes on spies congress and the united states intelligence community amy zegart hoover institution press 2011 cover support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9625 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
